h2 <a name="step3"></a>3. View your CO2 data

p.blurb You can retrieve CO2 data (as graphs, JSON, and CSV) using your feed's <b>PUBLIC KEY</b>.  They'll always be available (and free for you to share) at the following links:

pre
    code
        p <b>Feed Home:</b> http://data.pvos.org/co2/data/[PUBLIC KEY] <br>
        p <b>Feed as JSON:</b> http://data.pvos.org/co2/data/[PUBLIC KEY]/json <br>
        p <b>Feed as CSV:</b> http://data.pvos.org/co2/data/[PUBLIC KEY]/csv <br>
        //p <b>Feed graphs:</b> http://data.pvos.org/co2/data/[PUBLIC KEY]/graphs <br>

